subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen
. Subgenital plate with a broad, rounded posterior incision in male (
Figure 10B
) and it is similar and smaller in the female (
Figure 10D
). Cercus subcylindrical, and narrowed just before the apical tooth (
Figure 10A
) in male; female cercus subconical in dorsal view (
Figure 10C
) and without apical incision; measurements is 2.5–2.7 times longer than broad in male and 2.6–2.8 times in female. Ovipositor very elongate and provided with some dorsal, lateral and ventral rows of denticles (
Figure 8C
); it is slightly longer than the hind femur and is 2.3–2.6 times longer than the pronotum.
